Question: An object moves along a straight path from point O to point A (100 m away), then immediately reverses and stops at point B, which is 30 m away from A back towards O. What is the total distance covered and the magnitude of the displacement, respectively?
A) 130 \mathrm{~m}, 30 \mathrm{~m}
B) 130 \mathrm{~m}, 70 \mathrm{~m}
C) 70 \mathrm{~m}, 70 \mathrm{~m}
D) 100 \mathrm{~m}, 70 \mathrm{~m}

Question: A runner completes one round of a circular track of radius 175\,\mathrm{m} in 35 seconds. The average velocity after one round is ........ .
A) 0 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
B) 5 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
C) 20 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
D) 10 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}

Question: What is the chemical formula for Glucose?
A) \mathrm{C}_{11} \mathrm{H}_{22} \mathrm{O}_{11}
B) \mathrm{CH}_{3} \mathrm{COOH}
C) \mathrm{CH}_{4}
D) \mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{12} \mathrm{O}_{6}

Question: Which of the following chemical equations is correctly balanced?
A) 3 \mathrm{Fe}+4 \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O} \rightarrow \mathrm{Fe}_{3} \mathrm{O}_{4}+2 \mathrm{H}_{2}
B) 3 \mathrm{Fe}+4 \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O} \rightarrow \mathrm{Fe}_{3} \mathrm{O}_{4}+4 \mathrm{H}_{2}
C) \mathrm{Fe}+\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O} \rightarrow \mathrm{Fe}_{3} \mathrm{O}_{4}+\mathrm{H}_{2}
D) 2 \mathrm{Fe}+3 \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O} \rightarrow 2 \mathrm{Fe}_{3} \mathrm{O}_{4}+3 \mathrm{H}_{2}

Question: The measure of each interior angle of a regular pentagon is:
A) 128^{\circ}
B) 78^{\circ}
C) 118^{\circ}
D) 108^{\circ}

Question: Which of the following is equal to K if  \sin ^{2} \mathrm{x}+\mathrm{K}=1  ?
A) \boldsymbol{\operatorname { t a n }}^{2} \mathbf{x}
B) \cot ^{2} \mathrm{x}
C) \cos ^{2} x
D) \sec ^{2} \mathbf{x}

Question: A body moves along a straight line with varying speed. Its displacement in 10 s is 50 m. What is the average velocity?
A) 5 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
B) 25 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
C) 50 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s
D) 10 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}

Question: In quadrilateral PQRS, the bisectors of  \angle \mathrm{R}  and  \angle \mathrm{S}  meet at point T (inside the quadrilateral) and  \angle S T R = 24^{\circ} . If the ratio of  \angle P  to  \angle Q  is  3:5 , then what is the difference between the measures of  \angle Q  and  \angle P ?
A) 17^{\circ}
B) 12^{\circ}
C) 11^{\circ}
D) 15^{\circ}

Question: A car travels from City A to City B, a distance of 150~\mathrm{km}, at a speed of 60~\mathrm{km/hr}. On the way back, due to heavy traffic, the car's speed decreases. If the total time for the round trip is 7 hours 30 min, what is the speed during the return trip?
A) 42~\mathrm{km/hr}
B) 45~\mathrm{km/hr}
C) 36~\mathrm{km/hr}
D) 30~\mathrm{km/hr}

Question: An object is dropped from a height. What is its initial velocity?
A) 8 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
B) 10 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
C) Can't be determined
D) 0 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}

Question: Which of the following is a molecule of a compound?
A) He
B) \mathrm{N}_{2}
C) \mathrm{O}_{2}
D) \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}

Question: The law of refraction is valid for which range of the angle of incidence?
A) i > 90^{\circ}
B) 0^{\circ}<\mathrm{i}<90^{\circ}
C) 0^{\circ}<\mathrm{i}<45^{\circ}
D) 0^{\circ}<\mathrm{i}<60^{\circ}

Question: Which of the following is a double displacement reaction?
A) 2 \mathrm{Mg}+\mathrm{O}_{2} \rightarrow 2 \mathrm{MgO}
B) \mathrm{CaCO}_{3} \rightarrow \mathrm{CaO}+\mathrm{CO}_{2}
C) \mathrm{AgNO}_{3}+\mathrm{NaCl} \rightarrow \mathrm{AgCl}+\mathrm{NaNO}_{3}
D) \mathrm{Zn}+\mathrm{CuSO}_{4} \rightarrow \mathrm{ZnSO}_{4}+\mathrm{Cu}

Question: In quadrilateral PQRS, the bisectors of \angle R and \angle S meet at the point T (inside the quadrilateral) and \angle STR = 27.5^{\circ}. If the ratio of \angle P to \angle Q is 5:6, then what is the difference between the measures of \angle Q and \angle P?
A) 3^{\circ}
B) 5^{\circ}
C) 8^{\circ}
D) 2^{\circ}

Question: The length of the shadow of a vertical tower is equal to its height. Find the angle of elevation.
A) 75^{\circ}
B) 60^{\circ}
C) 30^{\circ}
D) 45^{\circ}

Question: The maximum number of electrons in a shell is given by:
A) 2 n^{2}
B) \frac{\mathrm{n}^{2}}{2}
C) 2 n
D) \mathrm{n}^{2}

Question: In  \triangle A B C, B D \perp A C  at  D  and  \angle D B C=76^{\circ} .  E  is a point on  B C  such that  \angle C A E=53^{\circ} . What is the measure of  \angle A E B ?
A) 55^{\circ}
B) 53^{\circ}
C) 78^{\circ}
D) 67^{\circ}

Question: The resistance of a metal wire of length 2 m is 10\,\Omega at 25^{\circ}C. If the diameter of the wire is 0.4 mm, what will be the resistivity of the metal at that temperature? [Given, \pi = 3.14]
A) 3 \times 10^{-7} \Omega \mathrm{~m}
B) 55 \times 10^{-6} \Omega \mathrm{~m}
C) 3 \times 10^{-5} \Omega \mathrm{~m}
D) 6 \times 10^{-6} \Omega \mathrm{~m}

Question: A ball is thrown up with a velocity of  \mathbf{x ~ m} / \mathbf{s} . The ball attains a maximum height of 50 m. What is the value of  x ? (Take the value of  g  as  10 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}^{2} )
A) 10 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
B) 1000 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
C) 10 \sqrt{10} \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}
D) 100 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}

Question: Nilu covers a distance by walking for 6 h. While returning, her speed decreases by  2 \mathrm{~km} / \mathrm{h}  and she takes 9 h to cover the same distance. What was her speed while returning?
A) 2 \mathrm{~km} / \mathrm{h}
B) 7 \mathrm{~km} / \mathrm{h}
C) 4 \mathrm{~km} / \mathrm{h}
D) 5 \mathrm{~km} / \mathrm{h}

Question: The approximate radii of hydrogen atom is:
A) 10-10 \mathrm{~m}
B) 10-7 \mathrm{~m}
C) 10-8 \mathrm{~m}
D) 10-9 \mathrm{~m}

Question: A train overtakes two people running along a railway track. The first person is running at 12.6~\mathrm{km}/\mathrm{hr}, and the second person is running at 25.2~\mathrm{km}/\mathrm{hr}. The train takes 16.8 seconds to pass the first person and 22.4 seconds to pass the second person. What is the speed of the train if both are running in the same direction as the train?
A) 59~\mathrm{km}/\mathrm{hr}
B) 62~\mathrm{km}/\mathrm{hr}
C) 63~\mathrm{km}/\mathrm{hr}
D) 60~\mathrm{km}/\mathrm{hr}

Question: From a shipmast head 210 m high, the angle of depression of a boat is observed to be 60^{\circ}. Find the distance (in m) of the boat from the ship.
A) 70 \sqrt{2}
B) 70 \sqrt{3}
C) 60 \sqrt{2}
D) 60 \sqrt{3}

Question: In quadrilateral PQRS, the bisectors of  \angle \mathrm{R}  and  \angle \mathrm{S}  meet at the point T (inside the quadrilateral) and  \angle S T R=28^{\circ} . If the ratio of  \angle P  to  \angle Q  is  3:4 , then what is the difference between the measures of  \angle Q  and  \angle P ?
A) 3^{\circ}
B) 6^{\circ}
C) 13^{\circ}
D) 8^{\circ}

Question: The length of a rectangle is twice its breadth. If the perimeter of the rectangle is 12~\mathrm{cm}, find the length and breadth.
A) Length =6~\mathrm{cm} and breadth =3~\mathrm{cm}
B) Length =2~\mathrm{cm} and breadth =4~\mathrm{cm}
C) Length =3~\mathrm{cm} and breadth =6~\mathrm{cm}
D) Length =4~\mathrm{cm} and breadth =2~\mathrm{cm}
